  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Feature Request / Idea : Allow persistency of artifacts remotely\r\n\r\nWe are currently using Truffle in an Enterprise project with Microservices, basically we have a dedicated container to deploy contracts using Truffle migrate command.\r\n\r\nThe problem is that each time we deploy a new version of the container the artifacts are not persisted. This is of course not a problem with Truffle, it is more about how we persist the data in Docker containers. Because we could just create a volume or an storage driver to handle this persistency issue.\r\n\r\nHowever, I was thinking that it would be nice if Truffle allow you to specify any remote storage like S3 or Azure so we can easily configure where to persist that information in Truffle config file.\r\n\r\nOther idea is to extend truffle migrations contracts maybe?  And store partial information like contract addresses there?\r\n\r\nThank you !",
  "closed_by": null,
